  <header class="main-hd">
    <h3 class="title">
      <a href="https://book.douban.com/review/1091835/" class="title-link">上帝的指纹</a>
      <div class="toggle_review right">        <a href="javascript:;" id="toggle-1091835"class="indicator unfold j" title="展开全文">        </a>
      </div>
    </h3>
    

<div class="header-more">
    <a class="author-avatar" href="https://www.douban.com/people/Ademina/"><img width="48" height="48" src="https://img3.doubanio.com/icon/u1290591-5.jpg"></a>
    <a href="https://www.douban.com/people/Ademina/" class="author">
      <span property="v:reviewer">格也</span>
    </a>    <span property="v:rating" class="allstar30 main-title-rating" title="还行"></span>
  <span property="v:dtreviewed" content="2006-11-19"
      class="main-meta">2006-11-19 14:20:57</span>
</div>

  </header>

        <div class="main-bd">
          <div id="review_1091835_short" class="review-short">
            <div class="short-content">
                  　　我对考古知道不多，不过我更倾向于把那些人们费力写下的所谓记实报告当作故事来读。不管怎样，一切都是推测，你不可能从这里得到确切的答案。但这本书能让我们对史前文明，包括对人类的发展产生探究的欲望。 　　那些神秘的遗迹，那些有相似之处的神话，在我们之前是否真有...

                  <div class="more-info pl clearfix">
                    <span class="left">2有用 / 1没用</span>
                        <span class="publisher left">
                            民族出版社1999版</span>
                  </div>
